    "For any given N, as r emp M M D → 0, p h → p δ.",
    "Thus our aim is to compute a control sequence u which leads to as low as possible r emp M M D. The K λ is a positive definite function in RKHS known as the kernel function with the \"reproducing\" property (6) [22], where ⟨•⟩ represents the inner product.",
    "Throughout this paper, we have used Laplacian kernel for which λ represents the kernel width.K λ (z, z ′) = ⟨K λ (z, •), K λ (z ′, •)⟩ H (6)Importance of Kernel Parameter:The kernel parameter λ critically controls the MMD metric, r emp MMD, by shaping the embeddings μ[h] and μ[δ].",
    "An overly large λ causes the Initial States Control Sequence MLP Point Cloud Feature Embedding Generate Distance Samples Generate Constraint Violation Samples Compute MMD Softmax MLP Risk Estimation Monocular Image Estimated Depth Map PointNet++ Architecture (CNN) Depth Map to Point Cloud embeddings to collapse to a constant, making them indistinguishable and insensitive to collision risk.",
